crops.institution_involved: School of Agriculture, Grootfontein, Middleburg, Cape
crops.description: Asteraceae. A rigid twiggy shrub with long erect branches and trifid leaves an inch or more long with linear lobes. The yellow flower heads are half an inch across. Part of a collection of plants native to South Africa, introduced for Department specialists (consignment 105936 to 105943).

crops.presented_by: Ellis Thomas, School of Agriculture, Grootfontein, Middleburg, Cape
crops.institution_involved: School of Agriculture, Grootfontein, Middleburg, Cape
crops.description: Asteraceae. A rigid, much-branched shrub, 1 to 2 feet high, with thinly silky tufted linear leaves up to an inch long and chrysanthemumlike flowers having reddish or yellow disk flowers and white rays. It is said to be a valuable pasture plant for sheep. For previous introduction see 93291. Part of a collection of plants native to South Africa, introduced for Department specialists (consignment 105936 to 105943).

crops.presented_by: Ellis Thomas, School of Agriculture, Grootfontein, Middleburg, Cape
crops.institution_involved: School of Agriculture, Grootfontein, Middleburg, Cape
crops.description: Chenopodiaceae. A dwarf shrub 1 to 3 feet high, with very small ovate or triangular, spirally arranged leaves and inconspicuous flowers. Part of a collection of plants native to South Africa, introduced for Department specialists (consignment 105936 to 105943).

crops.presented_by: Ellis Thomas, School of Agriculture, Grootfontein, Middleburg, Cape
crops.institution_involved: School of Agriculture, Grootfontein, Middleburg, Cape
crops.description: Aizoaceae. A much-branched, semishrubby perennial with fleshy leaves less than 1 inch long, varying from linear to ovate-oblong. The small inconspicuous flowers are borne in leafy racemes and are followed by 3- to 4-winged nutlike fruits. For previous introduction see 91238. Part of a collection of plants native to South Africa, introduced for Department specialists (consignment 105936 to 105943).

crops.presented_by: Ellis Thomas, School of Agriculture, Grootfontein, Middleburg, Cape
crops.institution_involved: School of Agriculture, Grootfontein, Middleburg, Cape
crops.description: Asteraceae. A bushy shrub 1 to 3 feet high, with alternate linear leaves, entire or 3-toothed, and numerous small flower heads. Part of a collection of plants native to South Africa, introduced for Department specialists (consignment 105936 to 105943).

crops.presented_by: James C. Scarffe, San Pedro de Macoris
crops.description: Cuttings presented by James C. Scarffe. Variety Porvenir-30: an erect vigorous variety which becomes 7 to 9 feet high; it matures in 5 months, is fairly drought resistant, and has never been seen with mosaic. Introduced for the use of Department specialists working with sugarcane.
